This is the revival of a software i wrote when i was still in university.
I liked the tool we used for a certain course, but it felt a bit antiquated, and naive little me wanted to make a new one.
At first i intended to sell it, but that wouldve meant more effort than it was worth at the time.
Time has passed and i have honed my skills, and a recent conversation has reminded me of this project again, so here we are.
This time open source though, no strings attached, no responsibilities. Lets see if i can make this work